1) find and replace a string in a directory

ex 

grep -rl 'windows' . | xargs sed -i 's/windows/linux/g'
grep -rl ":3306" . | xargs sed -i 's/:3306/:3307/g'

2)

reference 
http://www.fromdev.com/2016/09/powerful-grep-command-tips.html


to list all the files inside directory 

find . -name '*.php' | xargs wc -l





find and replace inside directory 

grep -rl '54.169.167.230' ./ | xargs sed -i 's/54.169.167.230/54.255.246.219/g'
